sentences: Rolf Liebermann (14 September 1910 – 2 January 1999), was a Swiss composer and music administrator.
He served as the Artistic Director of the Hamburg State Opera from 1959 to 1973 and again from 1985 to 1988.
He served as the Artistic Director of the Hamburg State Opera from 1959 to 1973 and again from 1985 to 1988.
He was also Artistic Director of the Paris Opera from 1973 to 1980.
Liebermann was born in Zürich, and studied composition and conducting with Hermann Scherchen in Budapest and Vienna in the 1930s, and later with Wladimir Vogel in Basel.
Liebermann was the director of the Hamburg Staatsoper from 1959 to 1973, and again from 1985 to 1988.

In the intervening years he served as director of the Paris Opera from 1973 to 1980.

At the inaugural Eurovision Song Contest in 1956, Liebermann acted as the president of the jury; being responsible for moderating and finalising the results of the seven international juries judging the competition.
In 1992 he served on the jury of the Paloma O'Shea Santander International Piano Competition in Spain.
In 1989, he was the head of the jury at the 39th Berlin International Film Festival.
